                <head>224. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>During a fifteen-minute meeting on September 24, 1972, President <persName
                        corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Henry
                        Kissinger</persName> discussed the situation in Uganda and also devoted some
                    attention to Burundi. For a transcript of the conversation, see <ref
                        target="#d258">Document 258</ref>.</p>
            </div>
